{"meta":{},"result":{"jobOpening":{"jobOpeningShareUrl":"https:\/\/curtinmaritime.bamboohr.com\/careers\/201","jobOpeningName":"Vessel Chef","jobOpeningStatus":"Open","jobCategoryId":"18376","departmentId":"18418","departmentLabel":"Marine Transportation","employmentStatusLabel":"Full-Time","location":{"city":"Long Beach","state":"California","postalCode":"90802","addressCountry":"United States"},"atsLocation":{"country":null,"countryId":null,"state":null,"city":null},"description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Location:\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 <\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Varies<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Department:\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Marine Transportation<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Reports to:\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Mark Kuehn, Food Services Director<\/span><br><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Schedule:\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Full-time; minimum 40 hours per week and as needed for projects. Long hours, short notice travel, weekend duties. May involve travel to several locations and extended stays outside of home port.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><br><\/p>\n<p><em><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Efficiency. Innovation. Integrity. These are our 3 Pillars. At Curtin Maritime, these core values are the framework for safe performance and operational excellence; proof of these pillars is evident in our people and our fleet. For 25 years, Curtin Maritime has been an industry leader in quality maritime solutions. We are a dynamic Marine Construction and Marine Transportation company experiencing rapid growth. Our team provides customers with a complete suite of maritime solutions, allowing us the incredible opportunity to work on unique projects in some of the most amazing places on earth.<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<p><em><span style=\"font-size: 13px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold\">THIS ROLE:<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">The Chef has responsibility for proper planning, preparation, and cooking for all meals at the facility and off-shore during jobs as needed. He\/she will be responsible for menu planning, ordering, and purchasing food and drink items to provide 3 meals per day for the crew while ensuring the highest standard of quality. In addition, the Chef will be responsible to maintain the inventory of snack items, plates, cups, and utensils and ensure an acceptable level of cleanliness and organization in the Galley on the vessel and off-shore. The Chef will provide oversight and guidance to all vessel cooks and boat crews by assisting with menu planning, shopping and safe sanitary practices.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold\">WHAT YOU\u2019LL DO:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Purchase all items required for meal preparation and serving<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Use your experience and creativity to plan menus for Shoreside and offshore meals<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Prepare and serve meals in a timely manner and according to the meal schedule<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Ensure cleanliness of the meal preparation workspace and serving area<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Manage the inventory of food, snacks and drinks to ensure adequate supply and minimize waste<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Train vessel cooks and boat crew members in safe food handling, meal preparation and sanitary practices<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Track and report expenditures to accounting using Excel<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Washing dishes, cooking and serving utensils, and linens<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Maintain conference room reservations on Outlook<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Menu planning and meal preparation for crew and off-shore staff as needed<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold\">WHO YOU ARE:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Possession of, or ability to acquire an MMC (Merchant Mariner Credential)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Possession of, or ability to acquire an TWIC<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Possession of, or ability to acquire an AB (Able-bodied seaman) endorsement, limited or unlimited.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 13px\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Possession of, or ability to acquire an <\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">STCW endorsement.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">5 years of experience as a cook in a commercial setting<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">3 years of experience as a prep cook<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Maritime or cruise industry experience preferred<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">High school diploma or equivalent required<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Culinary program certification preferred<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">SERV Safe food handler certification required<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Valid Driver\u2019s License with clean driving record required<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Ability to travel and live on board a vessel for extended periods of time<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold\">Mental Aptitudes Required:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Self-motivated team player with a strong work ethic<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Must be able to get along with office staff and vessel crew members<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Must be able to effectively communicate both written and verbally<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Confidence to initiate correspondence with crewmembers and staff<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Must always follow all Company and United States Coast guard rules and regulations<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Must comply with all work rules, including those that pertain to safety and health<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold\">Physical Aptitudes Required:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Must meet \u201cfit for duty\u201d requirements upon job offer (pre-employment physical and drug test)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">The employee must meet physical requirements including but not limited to, walking, stooping, kneeling, crouching, crawling, climbing up\/down ladders and stairs, negotiating uneven and moving surfaces.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Ability to maneuver through\/in\/around small and\/or confined areas within the<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Ability to stand and walk on nearly a constant basis; ability to work long hours each<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Specific vision abilities required by this job include close vision, distance vision, peripheral vision, depth perception, and ability to adjust focus.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">Ability to work when exposed to odors, dust, dirt, mechanical hazards, high noise levels, and potentially hazardous equipment.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold\">WHAT WE OFFER:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #212121; font-size: 16px\">Competitive Compensation<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #212121; font-size: 16px\">Generous benefits package including Medical (Dental, Vision, STD &amp; AD&amp;D\/Life Insurance at no cost for employee\u2019s coverage) with additional option to elect incremental Life Insurance for employee and dependents and choice to elect Health and\/or Dependent Flexible Spending Account<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 13px\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #212121; font-size: 16px\">Curtin Maritime is an equal opportunity employer. All applicants will be considered for employment without attention to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran, or disability status.<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<p><br><\/p>","compensation":"$300 - $425\/Day ($21.43 - $30.35 per hour)","datePosted":"2025-04-22","minimumExperience":"Experienced","locationType":"0","seekPromoted":false},"formFields":{"firstName":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"First Name"},"lastName":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"Last Name"},"email":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"Email"},"phone":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"Phone"},"streetAddress":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"Address"},"city":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"City"},"state":{"isRequired":true,"value":"","label":"State","options":[{"id":"2","text":"AK"},{"id":"1","text":"AL"},{"id":"4","